Project Structure
This repository includes:
    •   functions.php: Custom PHP hooks and directory-generation logic used in the WordPress functions.php file.
    •   /custom/: The core JavaScript (jQuery/Ajax) and CSS files that drive the EMDR game mechanics.
    •   /templates/: The directory structures and entry files served to users upon registration.

Prerequisites
To run this tool, you will need a standard WordPress installation with the following environment:
    1   CMS: WordPress
    2   Theme: Twenty Twenty-Four (or a child theme thereof)
    3   Page Builder: Elementor
    4   Membership/Subscription: Paid Memberships Pro
    5   Some version of Jquery.min.js. Place it in custom/resources/scripts.

Installation
    1.  Environment Setup: Ensure your server permissions allow for the creation of user-specific subdirectories as defined in the functions.php modifications.
    2.  Theme: Select a wordpress theme (This project uses Twentytwentyfour)
    3.  Functions.php: Copy the relevant code from the functions.php file in this repository into the one for your theme.
    4.  Generate assets: Create video backgrounds and target images. Upload to /resources and /targets respectively
    5.  Shortcodes: Use the custom shortcodes defined in the code to embed the game into your Elementor layouts.

